{
  "stem": "12029.3",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "He used to do the odd jobs.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "He used to-- but funny enough, whatever they told him to do, they used to do differently.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "They never have done it like they told him to do.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] Then my father one day-- we knew that my aunts were in Vegrow.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And one day, a man came who was a friend of ours.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And he told us that the two aunts with a child were killed in Vegrow.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "They were in hiding in the basement, and they couldn't catch the bread.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "They went up on the attic, and the Germans came there.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "My auntie had a gold bracelet to get off to give it to him.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "He shot her.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "My other aunt starts screaming, and the child, and they shot all three.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "When I found out this and they told me, I was a young girl, and I fainted.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "I loved very much my aunts.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And it was a very moving moment in my life.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "It was in 1942.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I was 18.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] Then my father said that life-- but my little cousin, we send out the night before the selection with a lady to be outside the ghetto.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "They put them there to a house, and they told that they will be able to get out of the ghetto.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But unfortunately, the Polish police caught them.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And the Polack came to us, and he told us that it has to cost so and so much money to let them free, that we paid the money.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And she was with this Polish family.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] And my father decided that I should go out from the ghetto.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Then we once used to have a maid, and her name was Stefania Skwierczynska.",
      "word_count": 14
    }
  ],
